caption: The food is delicious and the staff is friendly and so talented. They are a fantastic addition to the neighborhood. I highly recommend the wings and the pulled pork. I look forward to trying the their wine recommendations.
Got food with so much delay!

Reclaimed is doing it right!  We went for the food and wine pairing event and felt like we got an amazing deal! The food was on another level and we ended up buying 4 bottles of our two favorite wines.  The patio was heated and nearly all the tables were covered by an umbrella. We had the best seats in the house at the bar which was decorated in fall and Halloween theme which created a cozy and charming feel.  We came prepared to conquer the cold, but in the end, we left all of that in the car.  Can't recommend this place enough!

My new favorite place for COVID-19—safe winter outdoor dining. The food and drinks are great, the service was amazing, and the patio is so heated that I took off not only my coat, but my sweater layer. I will definitely be back.
Friendly service, great food!
Great, atmosphere,  staff and food.
Such a great little hidden gem 💎 They have a small little patio that’s quiet and perfect for a casual date night or girls night with some yummy BBQ food
Great staff plus, Bacon Brittle and Bourbon!

We got to enjoy a lovely evening here last night! Maplewood Beer tasting and oysters!! They were delish! Also had my first Bitter Southerner and lamb burger. Their seasoned fries were really yummy! The outdoor patio is darling!! Service was great! We’ll definitely be back again soon.
Captain Kirk, Our Server, Was Awesome...Very Informative!....Wings were Just ok, but The Deviled Eggs & Shrimp & Crab Roll Rocked!!
Tastes as good as it smells!
Great food, great people and great music!

Food was good. Had the chicken wings and pulled pork sandwich. Service was so-so. Place was not busy and took a long time to get a second beer or the check. BBQ sauce was very good  music was just bad.
Need to wear a mask in the bathroom
Super friendly place with an amazing staff and great food. Rob, the bartender, was very attentive and makes a terrific Old Fashioned.
Good food good music
Delish food and cocktails in a nice intimate atmosphere.
Warm and cozy spot with an open kitchen and attentive bar staff. The scallops and grits were amazing! Would definitely go back!

This is my spot, excellent selection of cocktails, wonderful fusion of those spirits into their food too. Food has been fresh and so damn tasty. I'm a big guy and though the portions were great, enough to get full and no need to take leftovers. I had the lamb burger, Mac n cheese, a killer corn beef sandwich, never nothing bad. Very good service with attention to detail.

Reclaimed has become one of our go to places! The food, music, and cocktails are all amazing. We have tried many of their dishes, and none of them have disappointed. The menu changes seasonally, which is another perk. You have to try the Mexican Martini!
Loved it very personal
best pulled pork
I absolutely enjoy the dishes and service, good location next to my house. The workers are always very friendly. Will visit here again.
I love what you've done with the place!
The food is delicious and the staff is so nice!!!!

We live around the corner and stop in regularly for the live music, great food and drinks. They demonstrate genuine appreciation for their customers. The ruben, shrimp app, deviled eggs, brussels sprouts are our regular choices. Lamb burger is excellent. Scallops and grits, delicious. Mussels are okay. Beatles brunch is delightful.
Loved this spot.  I need to go back asap
Food is delicious! Will be coming back. Great rustic divey feel to it and did I mention the food is amazing!? Because it is and if you dont at least try here you're missing out!
Good drinks
The staff was super friendly! The atmosphere was quiet when we went on Sunday afternoon. I really enjoyed my vegetarian red beans and rice. Can’t wait to go back.

We love this place! The staff is super friendly and welcoming. Excellent drink selection and unique food menu. We had the wings, lamb burger, red beans & rice, and pulled pork sandwich. Everything was prepared just right. The space is really comfortable and the vinyl LP collection was great. We're definitely going to make Reclaimed one of our regular haunts!

Really good food, nice, casual atmosphere (especially the back patio) and friendly service. The smell from the smoker made me swoon! And street parking is really easy! Must haves: smoked brussel sprouts (cooked to perfection with some bacon brittle& manchego!) and smoked wings (divine...no sauce needed)! I don't know about other nights, but on Thursdays they have 1/2 off bottles of wine and the wines are reasonably priced. Will definitely be going back!
Great food. Everything was 🔥!
Amazing food and ambience
Over priced. Bathroom is gross. The furniture is cool but the walls and doors are nasty.

Loved every bit of it! Great place for a date night if you hate big crowds and want good food. The Rueben was super solid, and all of the apps we ordered we really good. Parking was meh...but its Chicago.  *I've been here 5 times with my wife already and we love it. The Reuben needs to be a regular option, but I've never been disappointed.

Best restaurant on western great food kinda pricey but like the saying goes you get what you pay for. been coming here for about a year now and have yet to find anything nasty on the menu plus the drinks were good and strong, Brunch was also epic.  Would highly recommend the poutine from the brunch menu and from the regular menu the lamb burger and brusselsprouts.
Food was average for upscale prices. I wouldn't go back
Great food, service, beverages and ambience. Can't wait to return!
Delightful small eclectic place. The lamb burger was excellent and the mac &cheese was very tasty too. I like that they play LPs for music there, when there's not live music.
Pricey.

Just a bad experience. Bad food, outrageous prices, very rude bartender.
A welcoming, friendly highlight to the Lane Tech ‘hood! Delicious, straight forward food and drinks.
Excellent food and service. Special "shout out" to our server Laura. She helped make our night such a delight!
Great spot to grab a table for drinks, dinner and conversations with friends or on a date.
Great food with a fun, southern flare!  Love the atmosphere, cozy!

Had high expectations after reading the reviews but left very disappointed. The hostess was cold and not very friendly. The food was mediocre and overpriced. The pulled pork sandwich was very dry and tasteless. The fries were good. The vibe of the place was okay, they had live music, and the decor was definitely a highlight.

Place was legit and very hospitable. Was talking with the chef and we had a nice conversation. He was testing out a new dish and was kind enough to let me indulge on it. It was a scallop dish with cream and sweet pea sauce, a pickle relish with corn, that was out of this world. Simply to say it should make the menu. They're doing good food and great cocktails. But even better the people that work there.

Food was incredible. The owner Craig made my lunch, absolutely fantastic experience and listening to tunes from their record player. Very unique experience but man the food was delicious. The BEST wings ever!

This is a very cozy restaurant with delicious food.  the Rueben and scallop and grits, both were very good and generously portioned. Service was good, noise level was a bit loud but understandable for the space. Loved that there was live music that had a bluegrass/folksy sound. However, for the purpose of eating dinner it made it difficult to hold a conversation with company. Overall a great experience, I’m excited to come back for the brunch menu in the near future.
Fantastic brunch menu, neat place. Nice back patio as well.
Great ambiance and food!! Little escape from the city.

don't know when they opened but they need to work out a lot of issues.  The chef also needs to know that cooking scallops "sushi grade" is not a thing.  So when the scallops are ice cold and raw in the center and seared on the outside its called a screw up and you apologize and not try and make up a story.  Also watching a bartender measure wine in a measuring cup before pouring into a glass is off putting at best.
Cool atmosphere, tasty food and some great music.

My wife and I came here last night before the Cubs gsme. We had the bacon brittle, pork nachos, and the reuben. All were excellent. The staff was friendly and efficient. Good beer list. The atmosphere was great. Playing classic records as we ate. Definitely a 5 star experience across the board.  I'm looking forward to the Beatles brunch next month.
Great service, atmosphere, and food. Sat at the bar and listened to live music while eating (and drinking) dinner. Couldn’t ask for more.
Great staff, great place
This cute restaurant has a great patio, friendly staff and great food and drinks. I highly recommend the ranch water margarita and the pulled pork sandwich. Delicious!
Was in the back half indoors. Very hot. Not much air circulation. Service was great, wings were ok, rigatoni was great.

Great little neighborhood place. Yummy and unique  appetizers. They have a wonderful bacon appetizer that's sweet and spicy served in a little cup, deviled eggs are wonderful!!  Nacho's, hamburgers, french fries.  Drinks and food everything is top-notch.  Clean and great service.
Great place to share good food and drinks with friends and loved ones. Loved the goat poppers and deviled eggs.
The pulled pork was nearly tasteless and unimpressive. The service was average. The environment of it was the best part. It's quaint and creative.
Good food
Good ambiance, great place for music, out-of-the-ordinary delicious food (billed as Southern style). Very helpful staff.
Good food and live music. Nice neighborhood place worth the visit. Think I would be a regular if I lived in the neighborhood.
Great BBQ food.  Local owned not a corporate entity.
Very decent small plate options for the money.  Small place, nice atmosphere.

Atmosphere was nice. Music was fitting but it was a little dark to see the food. Bar and kitchen service were quick and attentive on a Tuesday.  The brussel sprouts were decent but not the best we’ve tried. We tried the candied bacon and deviled eggs and both were unique and tasty. Reclaimed’s wings were smoked and some of the best I’ve had in terms of flavor, moisture and texture.  For entrees we tried the lamb burger and venison loin medallions. The venison was so tasty that as soon as my girlfriend tried it she asked to trade before even trying her burger. It really was phenomenally good and this place is worth trying if only for the venison. The lamb burger was well executed as well with a nice Mediterranean flare. The party was moist and rich with lamb flavor.  All in all a properly good experience. The only two things I would recommend changing would be the dim lighting and the venison really should have come with a sharper serrated knife. The flavorful food and service made up for these shortcomings and I will absolutely be returning ($6 Old Fashioned’s on Tuesday dont hurt either).
Bbq shrimp, wow! Excellent cocktails and good music!
Very nice, trendy, a little rustic bar restaurant. Interesting menu and they have live music on weekends. Very good musicians, usually duos. Small, casual place.
Excellent cocktails!
Fun place, good food, friendly staff...

Reclaimed is a great place - it's just not entirely clear what place that is. The downstairs space is tight, with a tiny kitchen and an expansive and ambitious bar. The food I've had had been very good (try the scallops and polenta!) and the cocktails are inventive and well-crafted. They often have live music and the choices are excellent. The monthly Beatles Brunch is particularly fun.  But. While the service can be excellent, I've had just abysmal service there as well - forgotten orders, unplaced orders, unclear who is helping you, can't catch anyone's eye, etc. Nice people but perhaps not all trained waitstaff.  The commitment to music is great, but there isn't really a great space to set up there so they move them around a lot. Plus I've seen a lovely jazz duo playing right under a TV showing high-school basketball. Pick a lane.  Overall, recommended. Has a chance to be a bit more.
Great food, excellent cocktails. Quaint atmosphere, music by vinyl which is awesome. Dont miss the bacon brittle.
They are doing all of the right things, happy to see this place thrive. Get the Brussel Sprouts, they're incredible.
Great food and drink
delicious and fairly priced. great atmosphere
Great Music. They had an eclectic ensemble of 3 great Jazz musicians. Violinist, Guitar and Harmonica/vocalist. The Drinks were very impressive and the food outstanding. Highly recommend.
Love this place. Good food, the portions are a little small for brunch, but delicious. The staff are so friendly and sweet. Live music on Fridays, and great music the rest of the time.
Loved the food and the staff were so nice and the service was fabulous! Highly recommend for any meal or even for just drinks. High quality alcohol with affordable prices.
Good food, especially the brussel sprouts and lamb burger, nice beer selection and live music make it a must visit neighborhood place.

Great little place. Loved the ambiance, and the bartender played a great old Cheap Trick album while we ate. The wings were very good, if you like a smoky flavor, you'll love them! They recommended a great bourbon as well. Very friendly staff...go see for yourself!
This place is a great place not just because they play vinyl. The lamb burger is worth checking out on it's own. Friendly staff and owners. If you are close, check it out.
Amazing food and service!  The drinks are awesome. We ordered the classic old fashioned and aviation martini. For dinner, we had the scallops and rigatoni.  I highly recommend this place.

Between Lindsey (our server), the amazing food, and the quirky-disconnected-but-somehow-it-works decorations inside, my wife and I had an amazing time at Reclaimed.  We started with the brussel sprouts and corn & crab fritters (they're really just crab cakes, but they're really _good_ crab cakes) and loved them both. The brussel sprouts were soft and slightly charred with a light drizzle of cheese. When it was time for the corn and crab fritters, we were astonished that they were really full of crab and delightful! The lemon aioli complimented nicely without overwhelming the senses.  I went for the Reuben (on regular toast because rye should be outlawed) and my wife did the lamb burger. They were both fantastic. I had to take half the Reuben home because they give you so much corned beef! The lamb burger was served medium and was not dry, filled with flavor.  Our visit was punctuated by the helpful, friendly service of Lindsey. She was funny and helpful, but never really doting.  We will be back for sure! This place is relatively unknown now, but should blossom into another "must visit" venue in the St. Ben's subdivision of our North Center neighborhood.

So cute, friendly, delicious, a true neighborhood gem with surprisingly unique food, great beers and cocktails, solid live music, and a wonderful staff. It's kind of an island where it is and I really hope people continue to hear about it and come in!!

Been interested in trying this place on Western Ave for a while. Finally my wife and I got the chance. The service was adequate, but sadly the 2 items we truely wanted to try (really both of them) were not available at 8:30pm on a Friday evening ! Too bad.... The place was lively, not too crowded for a Chicago restaurant on a Friday night. Maybe we try again, maybe not..... again too bad.

It's a Friday before the 4th, and I have been meaning to try this place. It was one of my best decisions this year. Great food, great cocktails and even better service. Philip is a maitre d in disguise of a bartender. A musician playing his albums while crafting cocktails. Go here and enjoy good food, music and booze. It's not that complicated.
Philip at the bar is a pleasure and he knows his music. Lots of vinyl and lots of variety. Food was delicious and drinks were generous. Give it a try.

Awesome we tried every item on the menu and it was delicious. We were a party of 7 on a Saturday. Service was impeccable. Love the ambiance and live jazz.
